onent\ndef: \"A homodimeric protein complex that is capable of binding a range of carbohydrates and is involved in anti-inflammatory and pro-apoptotic processes.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:15476813, PMID:18777589, PMID:8262940]\ncomment: An example of this is Galectin-1 in human (P09382) in PMID:15476813 (inferred from physical interaction).\nsynonym: \"galectin-1 complex\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"galectin-2 complex\" NARROW []\nis_a: GO:0032991 ! protein-containing complex\nrelationship: capable_of GO:0030246 ! carbohydrate binding\nrelationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0043065 ! positive regulation of apoptotic process\nrelationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0050729 ! positive regulation of inflammatory response\nrelationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0098609 ! cell-cell adhesion\ncreated_by: bhm\ncreation_date: 2015-04-07T15:03:15Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770037\nname: glial scar formation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process by which central nervous system glial and associated cells assemble and stabilize a dense, organized glial border at the site of injury. This involves proliferation and reorganization of reactive astrocytes and NG2 glia (oligodendrocyte precursor cells), deposition of extracellular matrix components, and formation of a barrier that modulates inflammation and regeneration.\" [PMID:20012068, PMID:23904622, PMID:27027288]\ncomment: Distinct from connective tissue replacement involved in inflammatory response wound healing (GO:0002248) as CNS glial scars differ in cellular origin and molecular composition.\nis_a: GO:0002246 ! wound healing involved in inflammatory response\nrelationship: has_participant CL:0000127 ! astrocyte\nrelationship: has_participant CL:0002453 ! oligodendrocyte precursor cell\nrelationship: part_of GO:0150103 ! reactive gliosis\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30887\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n","exit":0,"description":"Search for target terms to use in logical d